<span class='talk-transcript__para__text'>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='567790' id='t-567790'>In 1988, I went to Moscow</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='570735' id='t-570735'>to interview artists of the Soviet underground,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='573850' id='t-573850'>and I expected their work to be</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='575723' id='t-575723'>dissident and political.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='578177' id='t-578177'>But the radicalism in their work actually lay</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='581235' id='t-581235'>in reinserting humanity into a society</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='584160' id='t-584160'>that was annihilating humanity itself,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='586343' id='t-586343'>as, in some senses, Russian society</span>
